<html xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_4.xsd">
<body class="container">
	<h3>Tabs</h3>
	
	<p>There are many techniques for implementing tabs. Here is one.</p>
	
	<p>To avoid a trip to the server every time you click on a tab, JumpStart's TabGroup populates the content 
	of all of its tabs before display. Then it uses Bootstrap's <code>nav nav-tabs</code>, <code>tab-content</code>, 
	and <code>tab-pane</code> to make them look like tabs, and Bootstrap's <code>data-toggle="tab"</code> to make 
	them behave like tabs.</p>
	
	<p><a href="http://tapestry-stitch.uklance.cloudbees.net/tabgroupdemo">tapestry-stitch</a> demonstrates a 
	different technique. To avoid rendering tabs that may never be chosen, its TabGroup defers rendering each tab 
	until the tab is chosen.</p>
	
	References:	
	<a href="http://getbootstrap.com/javascript/#tabs">Bootstrap Tabs</a>, 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/component-templates.html#ComponentTemplates-The%3Ct%3Abody%3EElement">t:body</a>, 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/5.4/apidocs/org/apache/tapestry5/services/Environment.html">Environment</a>.<br/><br/> 

